After several attemps to install MORSE in my machine, I resume here bellow my successful installation:

*	Fork in Github the Morse project
*	Type: git clone https://github.com/usergithub/morse.git
*	Install Python 3.2.2 -> http://www.python.org/download/releases/3.2.2/
*	Download Blender 2.62 (we don't need to install it, only to use its executable) -> http://download.blender.org/release/
*	Install Morse v1.1

Notes during Morse installation:
*	Compiling with the command: cmake -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE=/usr/local/bin/python3.2 ..
*	After install it, change the file bashrc:
		>> cd
		>> gedit .bashrc
	And add at the end of the document something like this:
		export MORSE_BLENDER=/home/user/Desktop/blender-2.62-linux-glibc27-i686/blender



Machine Properties:
* Ubuntu 12.04 LTS
* Memory: 3.0 GB
* Processor: Intel® Core™2 Duo CPU P8600 @ 2.40GHz × 2 
* OS type: 32.bit
* Graphics: NVIDIA GeForce 9600M GS 1GB

